  "body": "###### Info\r\n\r\n- **Version**: MyEtherWallet version 6\r\n- **Browser**: Chrome\r\n- **OS**: Windows\r\n- **Page Url**: https://www.myetherwallet.com/wallet/access/hardware\r\n\r\n###### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1- Go on https://www.myetherwallet.com/wallet/access and choose Hardware Wallets\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/89529968/150297610-0e18660c-63ce-48ed-9aa2-29b41bb122cf.png)\r\n\r\n2- Open your ETH/ETC/ETH recovery app on your Ledger device and establish the connection\r\n\r\n3- Click on the Ethereum derivation path to open the small window that allow users to add a custom derivation path\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/89529968/150298669-d86233ab-47d1-4e5b-85d4-9a2b125c87c6.png)\r\n\r\n4- Add the ETC derivation path _m/44'/61'/0'/0_ (or any other derivation path), add an Alias and click on Add Path\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/89529968/150298952-667db601-5d6f-477d-958e-a63ae83b34bc.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n###### What do you expect to happen?\r\n\r\nI expect to be able to access the addresses derived with the ETC path.\r\n\r\n###### What happens instead?\r\n\r\nI face the error message \"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'then')\"\r\n\r\n###### Screenshot\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/89529968/150299078-c9f1f096-3637-4d06-9cec-38ff35a33c62.png)\r\n\r\nThis issue prevents Ledger users from using a custom derivation path to recover funds (for instance if they mistakenly sent some ETH to their ETC account in Ledger Live). ",
